<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10114d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10114d">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10114d"> 114(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">D</font> gun</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[JMC tells his biographer about an encounter with brigands in a cab]</font> &ldquo;Well,&rdquo; I said, a trifle impatiently perhaps, &ldquo;go on. Don&apos;t stop in the middle of it. I suppose you drew your trusty pistol.&rdquo; John grinned. &ldquo;You guessed it. I did, &mdash; a nickel-plated thirty-two-calibre peanut shooter.&rdquo; &ldquo;You, a tenor, <mark>packing a gun?</mark>&rdquo; I was astonished; but I saw that McCormack was not exaggerating. <small> Pierre V.R. Key, Louis. <a name="PVRK" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#PVRK"><cite title="source">John McCormack: His own life story</cite></a> (1918) 135</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
